{"info": {"author": "Matthew Miguel", "author_email": "mmiguel6288code@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Intended Audience :: End Users/Desktop", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Natural Language :: English", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython"], "description": "# monoff\nWhen run via \"python -m monoff\", will turn off all monitors. \nTyping on the keyboard or moving the mouse should bring the monitors back.\nIf your monitors auto-detect digital inputs, they should switch to another source if one is available.\nMay be used to switch all monitors in one command in this manner as opposed to individually selecting sources on each monitor.\n\nShould work for Windows, Linux, and Mac. Not tested for Mac.\n\n## Notes for different platforms\n\n### Windows:\n\tRequires pywin32 (not installed automatically)\n\tUses pywin32 to broadcast an SC_MONITORPOWER\n\t[https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/menurc/wm-syscommand](Microsoft Documentation)\n\n### Linux:\n\tUses \"xset dpms force off\"\n\n### Mac (not tested):\n\tUses \"pmset displaysleepnow\"\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/mmiguel6288code/monoff", "keywords": "monitors,power,dpms,monitor,off,turn off,power down", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "Matthew Miguel", "maintainer_email": "mmiguel6288code@gmail.com", "name": "monoff", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/monoff/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/monoff/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/mmiguel6288code/monoff"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/monoff/0.0.3/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": "", "summary": "Simple script to turn off all monitors", "version": "0.0.3", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>monoff</h1>\n<p>When run via \"python -m monoff\", will turn off all monitors.\nTyping on the keyboard or moving the mouse should bring the monitors back.\nIf your monitors auto-detect digital inputs, they should switch to another source if one is available.\nMay be used to switch all monitors in one command in this manner as opposed to individually selecting sources on each monitor.</p>\n<p>Should work for Windows, Linux, and Mac. Not tested for Mac.</p>\n<h2>Notes for different platforms</h2>\n<h3>Windows:</h3>\n<pre><code>Requires pywin32 (not installed automatically)\nUses pywin32 to broadcast an SC_MONITORPOWER\n[https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/menurc/wm-syscommand](Microsoft Documentation)\n</code></pre>\n<h3>Linux:</h3>\n<pre><code>Uses \"xset dpms force off\"\n</code></pre>\n<h3>Mac (not tested):</h3>\n<pre><code>Uses \"pmset displaysleepnow\"\n</code></pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7011802, "releases": {"0.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "9c4545dbbb36c95d8a4ca492f63363f3", "sha256": "0e2144fa632b5fda544d821857634937b57211fc3dff4357d26261ecca6ebcc7"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "monoff-0.0.1-py2.py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "9c4545dbbb36c95d8a4ca492f63363f3", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py2.py3", "requires_python": null, "size": 3222, "upload_time": "2020-04-13T16:53:05", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-13T16:53:05.681789Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/e1/42/b0788fe7609ad5a975757f540cb1e5117b99612193f9769722b390bef4e2/monoff-0.0.1-py2.py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "7e703024e7439079372db2096a05a99b", "sha256": "7d6580fafa09e0fd95a4d1d43d2b7f439db275182d74a008597cbea796a8b4c3"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "monoff-0.0.1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "7e703024e7439079372db2096a05a99b", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requir